history.content: Ok, I just got through to a diploma specialist, and she said the diplomas (for undergrads) have been mailed (i.e. the order was placed) on May 9th. Some of the returns have just started to come in, so it sounds like if we had the correct address on file, the diploma should get there shortly. The guaranteed delivery date is June 9th, so if it doesn't arrive until then, she said to call her (I called CalCentral and was transferred to her) to see if the diploma has been returned.

I graduated last Fall and still haven't received the diploma. My CalCentral account shows that the degree has been awarded on December 14th, 2018. I'm a little worried at this point since the website said it would take four months, but now it's been five. I tried calling CalCentral, was transferred to some person there and was sent to a voicemail - left a message, but no one got back to me. Is this expected (I mean that the diploma still hasn't arrived)? I'll be moving next week and will be out of state for a month, and I'm worried that the diploma will get lost :/
